---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Hampstead Architects & Interiors"
  description="Our commitment to protecting your personal data and privacy in accordance with UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018."
  schemaType="WebPage"
>
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-light mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/60 mb-12">Last updated: December 27, 2025</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Hampstead Architects & Interiors ("we", "our", "us") is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you use our website or engage with our architectural concierge services.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are registered as a data controller with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) and comply with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Data Controller:</strong> Hampstead Architects & Interiors<br>
            <strong>Address:</strong> Palace Court, 250 Finchley Road, London NW3 6DN<br>
            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com">privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com</a><br>
            <strong>Phone:</strong> 020 7123 4567
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">2. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">2.1 Information You Provide to Us</h3>
          <p>When you submit a project inquiry through our website, we collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal identification:</strong> Name, email address, phone number</li>
            <li><strong>Property details:</strong> Postcode, conservation area status, freehold status</li>
            <li><strong>Project information:</strong> Project type, planning status, budget range</li>
            <li><strong>Consultation preferences:</strong> Preferred meeting method (in-person, on-site, Zoom)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-6">2.2 Information We Collect Automatically</h3>
          <p>When you visit our website, we may automatically collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system, device information</li>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, referring website</li>
            <li><strong>Location data:</strong> Approximate geographic location based on IP address</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 italic mt-4">
            Note: We do not use cookies or tracking technologies on this website. All data collection is limited to information you voluntarily provide and basic server logs.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">3.1 To Provide Our Services</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Processing and responding to your project inquiry</li>
            <li>Matching you with appropriate architects from our network</li>
            <li>Scheduling consultations at Palace Court or other locations</li>
            <li>Conducting feasibility reviews of your site and planning constraints</li>
            <li>Providing quotes and project proposals</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-6">3.2 Legal Basis for Processing</h3>
          <p>We process your personal data under the following legal bases:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> You have given explicit consent for us to process your data when submitting an inquiry</li>
            <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing is necessary for entering into or performing a contract with you</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> We have a legitimate business interest in responding to inquiries and providing architectural services</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-6">3.3 Third-Party Sharing</h3>
          <p>We may share your information with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Partner architects:</strong> When matching you with specialists from our network (with your consent)</li>
            <li><strong>Hampstead Renovations Group:</strong> Our affiliated construction company, for integrated design-build projects</li>
            <li><strong>Email service provider:</strong> Resend (for sending confirmation emails and notifications)</li>
            <li><strong>Planning consultants:</strong> For checking conservation area status and planning constraints</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="bg-warm-stone p-4 border-l-3 border-oxidized-copper mt-4">
            <strong>Important:</strong> We never sell, rent, or trade your personal data to third parties for marketing purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">4. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain your personal data for the following periods:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Active inquiries:</strong> Until project completion or 12 months after last contact</li>
            <li><strong>Completed projects:</strong> 7 years (for professional indemnity insurance and legal requirements)</li>
            <li><strong>Declined inquiries:</strong> 24 months (in case you return with future projects)</li>
            <li><strong>Email communications:</strong> In accordance with our email retention policy (3 years)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 mt-4">
            After these periods, we will securely delete or anonymize your data unless we are legally required to retain it longer.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">5. Your Rights Under UK GDPR</h2>
          <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Access</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Request a copy of all personal data we hold about you (Subject Access Request)</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Rectification</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Correct any inaccurate or incomplete personal data</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Erasure ("Right to be Forgotten")</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Request deletion of your personal data (subject to legal retention requirements)</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Restrict Processing</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Limit how we use your data while we verify accuracy or assess deletion requests</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Data Portability</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Object</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Object to processing based on legitimate interests or direct marketing</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Right to Withdraw Consent</h3>
              <p class="text-sm">Withdraw consent at any time (where processing is based on consent)</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6">
            To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com" class="text-oxidized-copper hover:underline">privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com</a> or write to us at the address above. We will respond within 30 days.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">6. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All data transmission uses HTTPS/TLS encryption</li>
            <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> Only authorized staff can access client data</li>
            <li><strong>Secure storage:</strong> Data is stored on secure servers with regular backups</li>
            <li><strong>Staff training:</strong> All team members are trained in GDPR compliance and data handling</li>
            <li><strong>Incident response:</strong> We have procedures to detect, report, and investigate data breaches</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="bg-warm-stone p-4 border-l-3 border-oxidized-copper mt-4">
            <strong>Data Breach Notification:</strong> In the unlikely event of a data breach affecting your rights, we will notify you and the ICO within 72 hours as required by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">7. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Your data is primarily stored within the United Kingdom. If we transfer data outside the UK/EEA (e.g., to email service providers in the USA), we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place through:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) approved by the UK ICO</li>
            <li>Adequacy decisions by the UK Government</li>
            <li>Certification under recognized data protection frameworks</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">8. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are not directed at children under 16 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe we have collected data from a child, please contact us immediately.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page indicates when the policy was last revised.
          </p>
          <p>
            Significant changes will be communicated via email to existing clients or prominently displayed on our website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">10. Complaints and Regulatory Authority</h2>
          <p>
            If you have concerns about how we handle your personal data, please contact us first at <a href="mailto:privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com" class="text-oxidized-copper hover:underline">privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK supervisory authority:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong><br>
            Wycliffe House, Water Lane<br>
            Wilmslow, Cheshire SK9 5AF<br>
            Tel: 0303 123 1113<br>
            Website: <a href="https://ico.org.uk" class="text-oxidized-copper hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-light mb-4">11. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, please contact:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            <strong>Data Protection Officer</strong><br>
            Hampstead Architects & Interiors<br>
            Palace Court, 250 Finchley Road<br>
            London NW3 6DN<br>
            <br>
            Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com" class="text-oxidized-copper hover:underline">privacy@hampsteadarchitects.com</a><br>
            Phone: 020 7123 4567<br>
            Website: <a href="/" class="text-oxidized-copper hover:underline">hampsteadarchitects.com</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-charcoal/10 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/60">
          This privacy policy was last reviewed and updated to ensure compliance with UK GDPR and Data Protection Act 2018.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

